# Laudius Kinclaith, alias "Silk"

Gentleman boxer con man. Member of [[The Creed]].

## Look

Blonde, handsome, put together, green eyes. Wears fine suits. Carries a cane sword.

## Concept

A British-style gentleman with a brawler underneath. Former fighting-pit boxer who ran scams throwing fights for money — the pit was organized by [[Bazso Baz]]. At least one rig was run together with [[Irimina]], screwing over a group of people from the docks — the fighter was supplied by [[Holtz Welker|Holtz Welker]]'s student, who took a beating to build long odds then pulled a high-odds reversal (a "Snatch-move" KO of the favourite). That match is how Laudius and Holtz met. Ostracized from the underworld when a killing exposed the scam; the pit was shut down, humiliating Bazso, who'd had no idea what was happening under his nose. Served time in [[Ironhook Prison]], fought in the prison fight ring, and met [[Harker]] there.

## Why "Silk"

- Boxers wear silk — robes and trunks
- "Taking silk" — the English phrase for a barrister ascending to gentleman rank
- Silk tongue — the con man's tool
- A silk cord is a garrote — the assassin's layer

## Heritage: Akoros

Akorosi "claim the same heritage as the Immortal Emperor himself, and base titles of nobility on this heritage" (p. 239). Cultures resemble Western/Eastern Europe. See [[Akoros]].

